1 and provides support to children of veterans or those with a deployed family member; and
2 WHEREAS, AmeriCorps is serving over two hundred eighty thousand special needs
3 children through a network of various organizations, helping to guide students to higher
4 academic achievement; and
5 WHEREAS, the AmeriCorps Seniors SUSLA Foster Grandparent Volunteer Program
6 matches the willingness and capacity of Caddo/Bossier FGP's volunteers to devote their
7 time, experience, and compassion with the needs of children to learn and prepare for the life
8 ahead of them; and
9 WHEREAS, this program continues to fulfill its mission of providing guidance and
10 support to disadvantaged children, while enriching the lives of the senior volunteers resulting
11 in better health and longevity having served their community; and
12 WHEREAS, AmeriCorps Seniors volunteers who serve with the Foster Grandparent
13 program provide the kind of comfort and love that sets a child on a path to a successful
14 future.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
16 does hereby commend the AmeriCorps Seniors Southern University at Shreveport (SUSLA)
17 Caddo/Bossier Foster Grandparent Volunteer Program for forty-six years of exceptional
18 service to children and does hereby extend best wishes for its continued success in the future.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
20 AmeriCorps Seniors of SUSLA Caddo/Bossier Foster Grandparent Volunteer Program.
